<seg id=1> The Irish Public Army  Declared Cease-Fire </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency. London. Aug. 31. (Reporter Li Wenhao) The Irish Public Army declared today, the organization will from this midnight thoroughly stop all military activities, and practise the "unconditional and no-time-limit" cease-fire. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> In a statement addressed to UK and Irish media, the Irish Public Army said that in consideration of the current siuation, to promote the peace course in North Ireland, the organization made the above-mentioned decision and informed all the subordinate troops of this decision. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> The statement requires the British Government to face the responsibility it undertakes, urge the parties concerned to face firmly and patiently the new situation brought by the cease-fire, hold an extensive negotiations, participants of which should include British Government, Irish Government and the principal parties in North Ireland, and eventually to solve the conflict in North Ireland. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> The statement says, the cease-fire declared by IPA offered an opportunity of "just and permanent" resolution of the North Ireland problem. </seg>
<seg id=6> IPA also reiterated that it would stick to its "Republic goal", e.g. the reunion of the whole Ireland. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> To realize the reunion of Northern Ireland and The Public of Ireland, the IPA has been undertaking violence activities in Northern Ireland for 25 years. </seg>
</p>
